\f2\i\fs28 \cf0 \strokec3 Dear Ir\'e8ne,\uc0\u8232 After various wanderings, we\'92ve arrived here, but we can\'92t make an attempt at working until we\'92ve made some modifications at the hospital. They want to build a shelter for the car and a partition to create the radiology room in a big ward. That all holds up the work, but it\'92s difficult to do otherwise. In Dunkirk, German planes dropped some bombs that killed a few people, but the populace is scarcely frightened. At Poperinghe too these accidents happen, but less often. We hear the guns grumbling almost constantly. It\'92s not raining, a bit of frost. We were welcomed at the hospital with extreme cordiality, I have a nice room and they give me a fire in a stove at the side. I\'92m better off than at Furnes, I\'92ll eat at the hospital. With a hug,
